pageContext.claim: “We achieved record low unemployment for African Americans, Hispanic Americans, Asian Americans, women, young people, young people without diplomas, with diplomas, with college education, without, and all levels of education.”
pageContext.analysis: For some reason, Trump always stretches this claim. Throughout 2018 and 2019, a low of 3.5 percent unemployment would be the best in 50 years, not more than 50 years. Even an unemployment rate of 3.4 percent would not be the best in more than 50 years. In 2019, the unemployment rate ranged between 3.5 percent and 4.0 percent.
